        "body": "## What\r\n\r\nCloses #2\r\n\r\nAdded a GitHub Actions CI workflow that runs automatically on every pull request targeting `dev` and `main`.\r\n\r\nThe workflow:\r\n\r\n* Uses Python 3.10\r\n* Installs project dependencies from `requirements.txt`\r\n* Enables pip dependency caching\r\n* Runs Black, isort, flake8, and pytest checks\r\n\r\n## How to Test\r\n\r\n1. Create a pull request targeting `dev` or `main`.\r\n2. Verify that the GitHub Actions workflow starts automatically.\r\n3. Confirm that Black, isort, flake8, and pytest are executed in the GitHub Actions workflow.\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n\r\n* [x] Tests pass (`pytest tests/ -v`)\r\n* [ ] Code formatted (`black src/ tests/` and `isort src/ tests/`)\r\n* [ ] No lint errors (`flake8 src/ tests/`)\r\n* [ ] Type hints on all new functions\r\n* [ ] Docstrings on all new public functions\r\n* [x] Updated relevant docs if needed\r\n\r\n## Screenshots / Output\r\n\r\nLocal verification completed using:\r\n\r\n* `black --check src/ tests/`\r\n* `isort --check src/ tests/`\r\n* `flake8 src/ tests/`\r\n* `pytest tests/ -v`\r\n\r\nDuring local testing, Black, isort, and flake8 reported existing formatting, import sorting, and lint issues already present in the repository. `pytest` completed successfully, but no tests were collected because the `tests/` directory currently contains only `__init__.py`.\r\n",
