        "body": "## What\r\n\r\nCloses #1\r\n\r\nMade a few fixes to get the Docker setup working locally:\r\n\r\n* Updated the package names in the `Dockerfile` so the image builds successfully with the current Debian base image.\r\n* Removed the deprecated `version` field from `docker-compose.yml`.\r\n* Temporarily disabled the frontend service in Docker Compose since the frontend scaffold isn't available yet.\r\n* Verified that the backend and PostgreSQL containers start successfully.\r\n* Confirmed the health endpoint is accessible.\r\n\r\n## How to Test\r\n\r\n1. Clone the repository.\r\n2. Copy `.env.example` to `.env`.\r\n3. Run:\r\n\r\n   ```bash\r\n   docker compose build\r\n   ```\r\n4. Start the services:\r\n\r\n   ```bash\r\n   docker compose up -d\r\n   ```\r\n5. Verify the backend:\r\n\r\n   ```bash\r\n   curl http://localhost:8000/health\r\n   ```\r\n\r\nExpected output:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\"status\":\"ok\",\"version\":\"0.1.0\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n\r\n* [x] Docker image builds successfully\r\n* [x] Backend container starts successfully\r\n* [x] PostgreSQL container starts successfully\r\n* [x] Verified the `/health` endpoint\r\n* [ ] Tests pass (`pytest tests/ -v`)\r\n* [ ] Code formatted (`black src/ tests/` and `isort src/ tests/`)\r\n* [ ] No lint errors (`flake8 src/ tests/`)\r\n* [ ] Type hints on all new functions\r\n* [ ] Docstrings on all new public functions\r\n\r\n## Output\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ docker compose up -d\r\n✔ Container engageiq-ai_2-db-1 Started\r\n✔ Container engageiq-ai_2-backend-1 Started\r\n\r\n$ curl http://localhost:8000/health\r\n{\"status\":\"ok\",\"version\":\"0.1.0\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
